{"_id":"3eEevBx686hBOFNt","name":"Hell's Wrath","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Diabolists channel fiery, Hellish power that can boil flesh and melt bone. Once this Edge is taken, the diabolist&rsquo;s bolt, blast, and burst powers cause +2 damage.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Diabolist)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kz0w6VzO7T0bdpdi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_c4ddko88oq9"}}}
{"_id":"4vXTcxjDIGvFgLVx","name":"Arcane Background (Bard)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Bards cast spells by singing, reciting poetry, or performing dramatic quotes. Some bards work their spells in other ways, such as captivating dances or farcical plays. They are usually erudite individuals, traveling the land to regale audiences with bawdy songs and epic poems.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Bard)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Performance (Spirit) </li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS: Boost/lower Trait, sound/silence and one other power chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>POWER POINTS: 10</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Arcane protection, banish, beast friend, boost/lower Trait, confusion, conceal arcana, dispel, divination, drain Power Points, empathy, fear, healing, mind link, mind reading, puppet, relief, sloth/speed, slumber, smite, sound/silence, speak language, stun, warrior&rsquo;s gift.  MAGIC: Bards may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Magic).</li>\n<li>ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Minor): Bulky armor interferes with a bard&rsquo;s grace and dexterity. They subtract 4 from Performance rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using medium or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n<li>SHARP TONGUED: Bards may use Performance as Taunt to Test a foe. They may also ignore the Repetition advice given under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as long as they recite different verses, stanzas, lyrics, etc. Bards may also substitute Performance for Taunt to meet Edge Requirements.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Sprit d6+, Performance d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7A8Mjvaua5QKEYmN"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2jnavlrmj8e"}}}
{"_id":"6CafOSqyVsLMsbRM","name":"Scorch","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This Edge improves the damage dealt by a breath weapon by one die type. A breath<br />attack that causes 2d6 damage, for example, does 2d8 after taking this Edge. It also<br />allows the fire breather to use either the Cone or Line template as desired.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Breath Weapon"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AV7Hb7PVfzG6IH5V"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
{"_id":"6E2MZFwWRaS4ZNtQ","name":"Troubadour","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Troubadours travel the world, learning culture, etiquette, history, and above all, legends.</p>\n<p>They add +2 to most Common Knowledge rolls (GM&rsquo;s call) and may use Performance<br />in place of Battle for Leadership Edges or Edges that require Battle.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Common Knowledge d6+, Performance d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.72C5GoRcOQvO69iI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9lrkhtldl9e"}}}
