{"_id":"7VoNWOBhuHSgV5bc","name":"Arcane Background (Diabolist)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Dwellers in darkness, demons from the abyss, or spirits from devilish dimensions are the servants of the diabolist. She conjures them to do her bidding, entrapping or binding these otherworldy entities to fulfill his most arduous tasks and bedevil her foes.</p>\n<p>A diabolist&rsquo;s Trappings always smack of corruption and deviltry. Their core power is summon ally, which conjures demonic, ghostly, or other malevolent spirits into the world.</p>\n<p>Their conjurings smell of brimstone, offensive powers use fire or darkness, and those around them may hear inane whispers as their summoned servants coalesce into existence.</p>\n<p>Diabolists aren&rsquo;t necessarily evil&mdash;they may just come from a place where such powers are common, or have decided to use the powers of the Abyss against those things that dare to leave its punishing environs.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Diabolist)</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Spellcasting (Smarts)</li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS: Banish, havoc, summon ally, and two other novice powers chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>POWER POINTS: 10</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Arcane protection, banish, barrier, blast, blind, bolt, lower Trait (but not boost), burst, confusion, curse, damage field, darksight, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, disguise, dispel, divination, drain Power Points, elemental manipulation (fire only), entangle, environmental protection, farsight, fear, fly, havoc, illusion, light/darkness, lock/unlock, locate, plane shift, protection, puppet, scrying, sloth/speed, smite, sound/silence, speak language, summon ally, telekinesis, teleport, wall walker, warrior&rsquo;s gift, zombie.</li>\n<li>MAGIC: Diabolists may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Magic).</li>\n<li>ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Major): Bulky armor interferes with a diabolist&rsquo;s complex somatic movements. They subtract 4 from Spellcasting rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n<li>CORRUPTION: Diabolists consort with extra-planar entities, most of them evil or at least mischievous. They have the Corruption Hindrance (page 28).</li>\n<li>SUMMONING: Diabolists may conjure demonic soldiers (page 191) with the summon ally power at Novice Rank, for four Power Points. At Seasoned Rank, they may call forth hellhounds (page 191) for 5 points. At Veteran Rank they may summon a nightmare (page 192) for 7 points.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NQePOI3EN19ttjJA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_c4ddko88oq9"}}}
