{"_id":"BfFod8rlXoMksYLQ","name":"Instrument","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Singing bards often use musical instruments to accentuate their ballads, striking chords or hitting high notes at particularly inspiring parts of their songs.</p>\n<p>Dancing bards may use streamers or swords as their instrument of choice, while oratory bards might incorporate elaborate props or masks.</p>\n<p>A bard who uses an instrument of some kind when casting a spell adds +1 to her Performance roll. The bonus only applies when Performance is used as an arcane skill. Of course the instrument requires one or more hands to play.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Bard)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0holoM1JpyiUqK3f"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2jnavlrmj8e"}}}
{"_id":"CgKUDqB3bIQmBTWS","name":"Trapsense","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Many adventurers become adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares<br />and traps. They get a Notice roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within<br />5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be Shaken or Stunned.<br />This works generally like Danger Sense but applies only to mechanical and magical<br />traps (see Traps on page 67).</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be Evaded, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores<br />2 points of Evasion penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be Evaded, anyone<br />warned may Evade at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p>Disarming Traps: A character with Trap Sense ignores up 2 points of Thievery penalties when attempting to disarm traps.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Thief"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.slwe2KfBqJwXkhWk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9lrkhtldl9e"}}}
{"_id":"EOWIFfqNUWmQzAjF","name":"Unstoppable","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The hero is a irresistible force of nature, undaunted by hardship and steadfast in the face of the most seemingly insurmountable obstacles. She has the Unstoppable monstrous ability (see Fantasy Companion p 169).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Vigor d10+, Iron Jaw, Nerves of Steel"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.dDFwZxni5cHYI5TT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ult6pu9nb1"}}}
{"_id":"F4EnVpjhiaadCKdb","name":"Arcane Background (Illusionist)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Illusionists are extremely limited in their power selection, but are masters of the incredibly versatile illusion spell. Some manipulate light to create mirages, others conjure ethereal phantasms, and some even trick the observer&rsquo;s mind into believing what isn&rsquo;t there.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Illusionist)</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Spellcasting (Smarts)</li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS: Illusion, light/darkness, sound/silence, and two other novice powers chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>POWER POINTS: 10</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Confusion, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, disguise, fear, illusion, invisibility, light/darkness, sound/silence.</li>\n<li>MAGIC: Illusionists may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Magic).</li>\n<li>ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Major): Bulky armor interferes with an illusionist&rsquo;s manual dexterity and the intense concentration it takes to maintain their visual chicanery. They subtract 4 from Spellcasting rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n<li>MASTER OF ILLUSION: The caster&rsquo;s illusion spells can fill a Large Blast Template and always have the Strong modifier for free. If a foe successfully disbelieves, however, he sees through all that caster&rsquo;s illusions for the remainder of the encounter.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wmf0xNyz45ZUz0EH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_omqixfvb2mh"}}}
{"_id":"GAwvdge5XQnlBMWw","name":"Well Prepared","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The wizard may activate a power that can normally be cast as an action as a limited free action. This costs an additional Power Point, but not only allows the wizard to cast a spell each round without incurring a Multi-Action penalty, she may also cast it while Shaken or affected by some other condition that only allows free actions.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Smarts d10+, Channeling, Epic Mastery"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.u8jxzAi6RYbsHXc3"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ult6pu9nb1"}}}
{"_id":"Gb7u0RKPQAWg3GXB","name":"Arcane Background (Alchemist)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Alchemists create potions, oils, elixirs, and other consumables imbued with magical abilities. Their potions aren&rsquo;t like those listed in the Treasure chapter&mdash;those last for years, require invstment of funds, and are created with the Crafting rules (page 153 of the Fantasy Companion).</p>\n<p>Instead, alchemists imbue their potions, grenades, and oils with the powers they&rsquo;ve learned. Narratively, their concoctions are created &ldquo;off-camera&rdquo; some time prior to their use. In game terms, they&rsquo;re &ldquo;cast&rdquo; as the player needs them&mdash;pulling various vials or containers from their alchemist&rsquo;s bag or bandoleer and activating them as needed.<br /></p>\n<p>ARCANE SKILL: Alchemy (Smarts)</p>\n<p>STARTING POWERS: Any three from the list below.</p>\n<p>POWER POINTS: 15</p>\n<p>AVAILABLE POWERS: Banish, beast friend, blast, blind, boost/lower Trait, burst, confusion, darksight, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, empathy, entangle, environmental protection, farsight, fear, fly, growth/shrink, healing, intangibility, invisibility, light/darkness, protection, puppet, relief, resurrection, shape change, sloth/speed, slumber, smite, speak language, wall walker, warrior&rsquo;s gift.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>POWER EDGES: Alchemists may not take Power Edges except for New Powers, Power Points, and Edges specifically noted for Arcane Background (Alchemist).</li>\n<li>POWER MODIFIERS: Alchemists can&rsquo;t use the Selective Power Modifier.</li>\n<li>ALCHEMIST&rsquo;S BAG: Concoctions are stored in an alchemist&rsquo;s bag, as are the ingredients, glassware, and other scientific equipment she needs to create them. An alchemist can&rsquo;t activate her powers without her bag.</li>\n<li>COMPONENTS: Alchemists&rsquo; potions, elixirs, pills, and grenades are expendable, giving them the Components Hindrance.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Activation</h2>\n<p>When an alchemist &ldquo;casts&rdquo; a power, the player must describe how it&rsquo;s delivered.</p>\n<p>Powers with a Range of Self or Touch are usually a consumable potion, edible, pill, salve, or oil. Fatigue from Critical Failure affects the recipient if someone other than the alchemist.</p>\n<p>Powers with greater Range use misters, bellows, or grenades, with a maximum Range of 12&rdquo; (24 yards). The alchemist &ldquo;throws&rdquo; the grenade or fires the bellows or mister with his Alchemy skill rather than Athletics or Shooting (but treats other projectiles normally). Critical Failure affects the caster normally&mdash;the grenade or mister shatters in his hand, showering him with noxious fumes that cause Fatigue.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Alchemy d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VErfscJTzRvM7BbU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rtqi0xm40m"}}}
{"_id":"Gtvag3kiSGR7CpRQ","name":"Arcane Background (Elementalist)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Those who practice elemental magic call on the planes of earth, fire, water, and air for their powers.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Elementalist)</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Spellcasting (Smarts)</li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS:<br />Elemental manipulation (native element only), environmental protection (native element only), and three other powers chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>POWER POINTS: 10</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Barrier, blast, bolt, burrow (earth only), burst, confusion, damage field (fire only), deflection, divination, elemental manipulation (native element only), entangle, environmental protection (native element only), fly (air only), havoc (air only), healing (water only), plane shift (native elemental planes only), protection, relief (water only), telekinesis (air only).</li>\n<li>MAGIC: Elementalists may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Magic).</li>\n<li>ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Major): Bulky armor makes it more difficult to channel power from the elemental forces. Elementalists subtract 4 from Spellcasting rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n<li>ELEMENTAL ORIGIN: An elementalist must choose her primary element when she first takes this Edge. All of her power&rsquo;s use that element as its Trapping. Additional elements may be embraced via the Elemental Master Edge (see below).</li>\n<li>ELEMENTAL SYNERGY: When the character is near a significant source of her chosen element, she gets a reroll on her arcane skill. Significant sources include a bonfire for flame, a lake for water, gale-force winds for air, or piles of excavated earth, stone, etc. for earth (simply standing on the ground, on natural boulders, etc. isn&rsquo;t sufficient to empower the mage).</li>\n<li>Conversely, if the element is in scarce supply, the mage subtracts 2 from her Spellcasting rolls. Thematically, this includes a water mage in a desert, an earth mage in a cloudship, a fire mage with no fire present, or an air mage in a deep dungeon or cave. If the element is essentially absent, she cannot cast at all.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zY8srSQDkrpm1Ugz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_fth8tduj86b"}}}
{"_id":"HYVlyF49aT0O5TQ9","name":"Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Warlocks (or witches if female) are magic-users who learn their craft from a mix of sources. They might learn a spell from an old wizard&rsquo;s grimoire, and how to concoct a healing brew from their grandmother&rsquo;s notes. Other powers may be acquired from shadowy beings that lurk in the dark woods, found in long-forgotten tomes, or taught to them by strange entities that promise them power in exchange for a taste of their earthly beauty, charm&mdash;or life itself.</p>\n<p>Warlocks and witches are often feared, even by those communities they serve. Desperate locals quietly seek their aid in times of personal crisis, but may chastise them by day&mdash;or even participate in a &ldquo;witch hunt&rdquo; should some calamity be attributed to their &ldquo;consorting with dark spirits.&rdquo; For this reason, even good warlocks and witches tend to be wary, protective, and secretive. Those of a more vengeful nature retaliate in terrible ways, inflicting curses and other maladies on the populations who persecute them.</p>\n<p>EDGE: Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)</p>\n<p>ARCANE SKILL: Spellcasting (Smarts) </p>\n<p>STARTING POWERS: Any three chosen from the list below.</p>\n<p>STARTING POWER POINTS: 10</p>\n<p>AVAILABLE POWERS: Arcane protection, banish, barrier, beast friend, blast, blessing, blind, bolt, boost/lower Trait, burrow, burst, confusion, conjure item, curse, darksight, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, disguise, dispel, divination, drain Power Points, elemental manipulation, empathy, entangle, environmental protection, farsight, fear, fly, growth/shrink, havoc, healing, illusion, invisibility, light/darkness, lock/unlock, locate, mystic intervention, object reading, mind reading, mind wipe, protection, puppet, relief, scrying, shape change, sloth/speed, slumber, smite, sound/silence, speak language, stun, summon animal, summon ally, summon animal, telekinesis, wall walker, warrior&rsquo;s gift, wish.</p>\n<p>MAGIC: Witches/warlocks may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Magic).</p>\n<p>ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Major): Warlocks and witches must move quietly, make intricate somatic gestures, and access their hex bags. They subtract 4 from Spellcasting rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using light, medium, or heavy armor or shields.</p>\n<p>COMPONENTS: Witches and warlocks require bits and baubles for their spells, from eye of newt to the hair of a hanged man. They have the Components Hindrance (page 28).</p>\n<p>CORRUPTION: Warlocks and witches gather power and knowledge from a&nbsp; variety of sources, some of which bring ruin to their mind and body. They have the Corruption Hindrance.</p>\n<p>COVEN: Though warlocks and witches tend to live alone in isolated areas of the world, they occasionally gather with others of their kind to exchange knowledge, cast rituals, or fight some common threat. Covens tend to have an odd number of members, and no more than 13 at a time.</p>\n<p>Witches and warlocks may freely transfer Power Points between other members of their coven at any time. This may be done even when it isn&rsquo;t their turn, though the spellcasters must be within 12&rdquo; (24 yards) of each other. They do not need line of sight to transfer Power Points.</p>\n<p>FAMILIAR: Witches and warlocks maintain their connection to the natural world via small magical pets. They start with the Familiar Edge (page 36).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eRBRT4PZC6q7DZLa"},"cf":{"id":"temp_b0alwhlbt6"}}}
{"_id":"I8C9gq4iFSUekOzD","name":"Tinkerer's Armor","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The tinkerer modifiers her armor with cleverly placed springs, elastic straps, and reinforced bracers.</p>\n<p>As long as the tinkerer wears at least leather armor and has four hours and some material odds and ends to make the proper adjustments, she can reduce the Minimum Strength of leather armor (+2) or greater by one die type. She may also choose any one of the following effects, which she may alter with a minute&rsquo;s work and a Repair roll:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ARMS: The tinkerer adds +2 to her melee damage and gets a free reroll on Strength rolls (not damage rolls).</li>\n<li>TORSO: Increase the Armor value of the chest and back by +2.</li>\n<li>LEGS: The tinkerer can jump twice her normal distance and adds +4 to her Pace.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Breakdown</strong>: Any time the wearer suffers a Wound, roll a die. Odd, the armor&rsquo;s additional effect falls apart and requires four hours work and a Repair roll to replace the appropriate mechanisms.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Tinkerer)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DXvQ0NLGuJNvU5wv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2doysmr4wk7"}}}
{"_id":"IFocF7XfDcfdKNxT","name":"Defender","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>You can give an adjacent ally your shield&rsquo;s Parry bonus as a limited free action. This<br />deprives your selfless hero of the bonus in the interim. Shield bonuses don&rsquo;t stack,<br />so use only the highest if a character is protected by more than one.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pyOXDWAHFywsJGhZ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
{"_id":"IHbDgkl294DomPFA","name":"Ferocious Summoning","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>A summoner with this Edge has learned to conjure fiercer, more experienced beasts with the summon monster power. He may grant them any one Combat Edge of his Rank or lower.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Summoner), summon monster"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ELwtCAXRrwCedkny"},"cf":{"id":"temp_txmjdapapja"}}}
{"_id":"IY6ITK3gTUgz20JI","name":"Stunning Blow","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The character&rsquo;s blows are powerful or precise enough to stun his foes. If he strikes<br />an opponent with a blunt weapon (a hammer, maul, mace, his hands, etc.)<br />and causes at least a Shaken or Wound result, resolve damage and any attempt to<br />Soak. Then the victim must make a Vigor roll or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Strength d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.72h7KkE1GbHM60O1"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
{"_id":"JMmwenZeFIQoO2xo","name":"Double Shot","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Double Shot works exactly like the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rapid Fire]{Rapid Fire Edge} but with any sort of regular bow<br />(not crossbows). As a limited action, the archer may increase her weapon&rsquo;s Rate of<br />Fire by 1. The attacker must have a handy source of arrows to accomplish the feat (a<br />quiver, several arrows stuck in the ground at her side, etc.)</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shooting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oJvwM4yPWTDynrRz"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
{"_id":"KF7TybUxjHcsKYbb","name":"Mystic Powers","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>In worlds where magic is relatively common, disciplined adventurers may<br />learn a few simple powers to help them in their quests.</p>\n<p><br />Choose one of the packages below. The character has 10 dedicated Power Points<br />that recharge normally. As a limited free action, the hero automatically activates<br />the power with success for its regular cost, or with a raise for an additional 2 Power<br />Points. She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired (at the usual cost).<br />Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background,<br />but she may take the Power Points or Soul Drain Edge. If the hero also has an Arcane<br />Background, none of its Edges or abilities can be used with Mystic Powers and vice-<br />versa.</p>\n<p><br /> BARBARIAN (Strength d8+): Boost Trait<br />(Fighting, Strength, Spirit, or Vigor only),<br />smite, and speed. All have the Self<br />Limitation.</p>\n<p><br /> FIGHTER (Fighting d8+): Boost Trait<br />(Fighting, Shooting, Strength, and Vigor<br />only), protection, and smite. All have the<br />Self Limitation.</p>\n<p><br /> MONK (Athletics d8+): Boost Trait (Agility,<br />Athletics, Fighting, and Spirit only),<br />deflection, and smite. All have the Self<br />Limitation.</p>\n<p><br /> PALADIN (Spirit d8+): Boost Trait (Fighting<br />and Spirit only), healing, protection,<br />sanctuary and smite. All but healing have<br />the Self Limitation, but the paladin<br />gains no benefit from the Limitation.<br /> RANGER (Survival d8+): Beast friend, boost<br />Trait (Athletics, Shooting, and Survival<br />only), entangle, and farsight. All have the<br />Self Limitation.</p>\n<p><br /> ROGUE (Thievery d8+): Boost Trait<br />(Athletics, Stealth, and Thievery only),<br />darksight, lock/unlock, and wall walker. All<br />have the Self Limitation.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned; other Requirements are listed in the specific packages below."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XLd3qtZkwEQOjrSH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y0bdbtf8jfd"}}}
