{"_id":"Kt5d6NWPQMP8J1eA","name":"Spellbooks","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>A wizard&rsquo;s spellbooks contain copious notes on magical processes, arcane observations, and thaumaturgical insights. Whenever he takes the New Powers Edge, he gets three new powers instead of two.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Wizard)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pJt9qwjqnjB2mNDd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3666mrdr5op"}}}
{"_id":"LETOMInLbNGoLryI","name":"Master of Illusion","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The caster&rsquo;s illusions have the Mobility and Sound Power Modifiers at no additional Power Point cost.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Illusionist), Spellcasting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BW2lCWt0sF2ZKMvs"},"cf":{"id":"temp_omqixfvb2mh"}}}
{"_id":"LEUVdCHBoLFR5I8k","name":"Arcane Background (Shaman)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Shamans are the spiritual backbone of those who choose to live far from the corrupting influence of civilization. They make great use of the natural world, worshiping it and exploiting it for the good of others.</p>\n<p>Some shamans are hedge wizards or herbalists who use natural methods to produce their magic. Others are holy men or women who commune with ancient spirits of nature to do their bidding. All are as capable of blasting their enemies with the raw energies of the cosmos as reading the future in a pile of bones.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Shaman)</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Faith (Spirit)</li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS: Arcane protection, relief, and three other powers chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>STARTING POWER POINTS: 10</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Arcane protection, banish, barrier, beast friend, blast, blessing, blind, bolt, boost/lower Trait, burrow, burst, confusion, damage field, darksight, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, disguise, dispel, divination, drain Power Points, elemental manipulation, empathy, entangle, environmental protection, farsight, fear, havoc, healing, mystic intervention, object reading, protection, relief, resurrection, shape change, sloth/speed, slumber, smite, sound/silence, speak language, stun, summon animal, summon monster, wall walker, warrior&rsquo;s gift.</li>\n<li>MIRACLES: Shamans may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Miracles).</li>\n<li>FETISH: Shamans use a fetish connected to their tribe, people, or culture to focus their powers. This is usually a hand-held stick draped in bones or tokens that carry some special significance to them. Without the fetish, a shaman subtracts 2 from her arcane skill rolls.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Faith d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7U2bgCGUb0bqcF8P"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5mq23yfn8pg"}}}
{"_id":"LV434MPGSaokmuls","name":"Soul Jar","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The necromancer&rsquo;s mastery over the dark arts has finally allowed him to cheat death by hiding his soul.</p>\n<p>Doing so turns the necromancer Undead, though he may continue to look alive and well for the duration of his natural lifespan. Eventually, however, time takes its toll, and the necromancer&rsquo;s true state becomes visible.</p>\n<p>Choose a small to medium size vessel: a gemstone, a statuette, skull, vase, sword, etc. to act as the soul&rsquo;s container. If the lich is slain, the soul inhabits a new corpse 2d6 days later. If the vessel is destroyed, the soul is destroyed as well, so most necromancers hide their soul jars in a vault or other secure location.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Arcane Background (Necromancer), Occult d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JIC6MOnqRAHP5C3S"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f045umf8w76"}}}
{"_id":"LZ3V81UyuPPg1cMy","name":"Infernal Armor","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>As an action, a diabolist can lime her clothes (or armor if wearing any) with a Hellish glow that grants her +2 armor. This lasts as long as the diabolist wishes, but marks her as a channeler of dark magic and makes Stealth virtually impossible.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Diabolist)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QUy2dXPb80FOCzdY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_c4ddko88oq9"}}}
{"_id":"M4l8IT6S6kT66wRe","name":"Battle Magic","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This Edge allows the user to cast her spells on large units of Extras such as soldiers,<br />henchmen, or guards. See Battle Magic in the Fantasy Companion on page 98 for more details.</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Battle Magic Penalty</h2>\n<table style=\"width: 98.0611%; height: 103px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.8px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 48.9252%; height: 16.8px;\">Number Affected</td>\n<td style=\"width: 51.0399%; height: 16.8px;\">Penalty</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.8px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 48.9252%; height: 16.8px;\">2-50</td>\n<td style=\"width: 51.0399%; height: 16.8px;\">-2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.8px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 48.9252%; height: 16.8px;\">51-250</td>\n<td style=\"width: 51.0399%; height: 16.8px;\">-4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.8px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 48.9252%; height: 16.8px;\">251-500</td>\n<td style=\"width: 51.0399%; height: 16.8px;\">-6</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.geygBV4qwIrQFn4f"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y0bdbtf8jfd"}}}
{"_id":"M5HvTGyI8JGj9qBc","name":"Relic","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Powerful magic items should normally be discovered only through epic quests, dangerous treks into vast dungeons, or exchanging vast quantities of gold and other treasure.</p>\n<p>If those opportunities don&rsquo;t present themselves, a hero may take this Edge to choose any one magical item from this the Fantasy Companion. The Game Master must approve the choice as usual, deciding if such a thing even exists in her world. If so, the hero comes upon it somehow&mdash;perhaps via inheritance, at the end of the next quest, as a gift from those she aided.</p>\n<p>If the item is lost, she eventually recovers or replaces it, but may have to do without a session or two to recover it.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lGmvrNAQv7q3smZo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ult6pu9nb1"}}}
