{"_id":"PqVldcXdCgv9rj0j","name":"Arcane Background (Summoner)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>These mages specialize in summoning creatures from the natural world or other planes of existence to bear their burdens for them. They are similar to diabolists except their servants are typically of animal intelligence, and while fierce, are no more malevolent in intent than any other beast.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Summoner)</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Spellcasting (Smarts) STARTING POWERS: Boost/lower Trait (Limitation: Summoned creatures only), summon ally, and two other powers chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>POWER POINTS: 15</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Boost/lower Trait, summon ally, summon animal, summon monster.</li>\n<li>MAGIC: Summoners may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Magic).</li>\n<li>-1 ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Minor): Bulky armor interferes with the somatic gestures needed to communicate with summoned minions. Summoners subtract 4 from Faith rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using medium or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n<li>2 MASTER SUMMONER: A summoner reduces the cost of summon ally, summon animal, and summon monster by 2 (to a minimum of 1), and the spells&rsquo; Durations are measured in minutes rather than rounds.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ClPIhayTObYQTKQr"},"cf":{"id":"temp_txmjdapapja"}}}
{"_id":"Pzf5f6GZcOVSuODW","name":"Formation Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The warrior has trained to fight alongside others, overwhelming their common foe<br />with synchronized strikes and blows. She adds +2 to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus instead of<br />+1. The maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus is still +4 no matter how many Formation Fighters<br />stand together.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VPwL4pn6g8kqO1hk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9hfm5sf8y2i"}}}
{"_id":"Q5GB55sWOnvFQvge","name":"Fey Blood","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Elves, half-elves, and certain fey are often resistant to hostile magic. Those with<br />some amount of it in their blood get a free reroll when resisting enemy powers and<br />spell-like effects. This stacks with Arcane Resistance.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FCcDOYCLmpqxNqzQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zum629z8a7t"}}}
{"_id":"Qe4v5pe2pSnxAdpy","name":"The Evil Eye","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Powerful witches and warlocks are known for their baleful stares. Locals call this the &ldquo;evil eye,&rdquo; even if the mage is actually pure of heart.</p>\n<p>Once per encounter, a witch can target an intelligent being within 6&rdquo; (12 yards). For the rest of that encounter, the target must make a Spirit roll at &ndash;2 to spend a Benny.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Warlock/Witch)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hxBYM6m5G7UMJXRU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_b0alwhlbt6"}}}
