{"_id":"RlHWkpYHGWA4iWEf","name":"Arcane Barding","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The caster&rsquo;s animals appear swathed in eldritch barding forged from magical energies. This increases their Toughness by +2 and cannot be dispelled.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Summoner), summon animal"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iKBgcat0Eo1hF8Vi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_txmjdapapja"}}}
{"_id":"RpTzuX96WRLnTCBP","name":"Construct Familiar","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The tinkerer gains a magically animated animal companion made of metal, clockwork gears, or other machina. This works exactly like the Familiar Edge (page 36 of the Fantasy Companion) except the creature gains the Construct ability: Constructs add +2 when attempting to recover from being Shaken, ignore 1 point of Wound penalties, don&rsquo;t breathe or eat and are immune to disease and poison, don&rsquo;t Bleed Out, and Wounds are removed with Repair instead of Healing with no &ldquo;Golden Hour.&rdquo;</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Tinkerer)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YHwA2iCqyebtVYOy"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2doysmr4wk7"}}}
{"_id":"TeavTW2vKGhKn0F6","name":"Sacred Fetish","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Fetishes are devices that help a shaman focus her powers. A sacred fetish is one that&rsquo;s been blessed or sanctified in some way. As long as she has the fetish in hand on prominently displayed on her person, she gets one free reroll whenever she fails a Faith roll.</p>\n<p>Should a sacred fetish be lost or destroyed, the shaman may replace it by visiting her tribe for some item of sentimental worth or creating a new device that captures the essence of her people.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background, (Shaman), Faith d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.My9o7LNSZNjlXGry"},"cf":{"id":"temp_5mq23yfn8pg"}}}
{"_id":"ULlqduHA8HCxnojq","name":"Trick shot","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>When performing a &nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} with the Athletics or Shooting skill, the<br />archer can choose to make the foe resist with Smarts instead of Agility.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Athletics d8+ or Shooting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.nG63AoWY3A20nRZh"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
