{"_id":"YyzcIy3VLm99i9Fp","name":"Aura of Courage","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>A field of holy energy encircles this noble being. Allies within 10&rdquo; (20 yards) add +1 to Fear checks and subtract 1 from Fear Table results.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hagLRHKdxo1dOKve"},"cf":{"id":"temp_d3m3ewwj98g"}}}
{"_id":"ZBm1MyalGhhHCE1e","name":"Favored Enemy","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Your hero has fought a particular type of enemy for many years. She knows how<br />best to attack and defend against them, and where their weak spots are.</p>\n<p>Choose one type of enemy native to your character&rsquo;s homeland. Work with the<br />Game Master to define types, but typical categories include dragons, undead, spirits,<br />animals, fey, constructs, demons, and so on. &ldquo;Humanoids&rdquo; includes all Normal and<br />Small Size beings with relatively human-like forms. Monstrous humanoids include<br />any human-like Large or greater being.</p>\n<p>Your hero doesn&rsquo;t trust or like members of that race (&ndash;2 to Persuasion rolls when interacting with them), but knows how to fight them. She gets one free reroll when failing to track (Survival) or attack (Athletics (throwing), Fighting, Shooting) that type of being.</p>\n<p>You may take this Edge more than once to reflect experience with multiple types<br />of foes.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rcM9O544WsYqQOUT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zum629z8a7t"}}}
{"_id":"ZFEBkX2zFai07xmq","name":"Treasure Hunter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Tomb raiders and treasure hunters know what to look for when rifling through piles<br />of gold and goods. When the Game Master rolls for magic items (see Treasure on page<br />133), you can spend a Benny to have her roll again.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Notice d8+, Occult d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8ZtopybKprsGmj61"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3wjknv5js85"}}}
{"_id":"a1SSwH20FQHLIlwY","name":"Chemist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The alchemist&rsquo;s concoctions last one week rather than 48 hours when given to others. See the Alchemist Arcane Background on page 78 for more information.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Alchemist), Alchemy d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.R1ffMnoZrDl0uFA7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rtqi0xm40m"}}}
{"_id":"aKUUp2m0PXarho0J","name":"Arcane Background (Sorcerer)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Sorcerers channel and embrace the raw power of the cosmos. They treat with great and ancient forces greater even than the gods. They wreak terrible havoc, and inevitably pay an even more terrible price.</p>\n<p>Sorcerers brim with raw power, usually taken by force or subterfuge from some ancient and unknowable source. Occasionally they catch the attention of this font and its dark eye latches onto them, searing the sorcerer&rsquo;s soul with its unholy gaze.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>EDGE: Arcane Background (Sorcerer)</li>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Spellcasting (Smarts)</li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS: Three powers chosen from the list below.</li>\n<li>STARTING POWER POINTS: 15</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Arcane protection, banish, barrier, beast friend, blast, blessing, blind, bolt, boost/lower Trait, burrow, burst, confusion, damage field, darksight, deflection, detect/conceal arcana, disguise, dispel, divination, drain Power Points, elemental manipulation, empathy, entangle, environmental protection, farsight, fear, havoc, healing, mystic intervention, object reading, protection, relief, resurrection, shape change, sloth/speed, slumber, smite, sound/silence, speak language, stun, summon ally, summon animal, summon monster, wall walker, warrior&rsquo;s gift.</li>\n<li>ARMOR INTERFERENCE (Minor): Bulky armor interferes with the somatic gestures needed to steal mana from their source. Sorcerers subtract 4 from Faith rolls and Agility and Agility-based skill rolls if using medium or heavy armor or shields.</li>\n<li>CRITICAL FAILURE: Sorcerers who roll a Critical Failure on a Spellcasting roll are Fatigued, Stunned, and gain Corruption (see below).</li>\n<li>CORRUPTION: Sorcerers entreat with ancient, powerful, and distant masters. Sometimes those FANTASY COMPANION entities&rsquo; touch brings ruin on the spellcaster&rsquo;s body and soul. They have the Corruption Hindrance.</li>\n<li>OVERPOWER: As long as they don&rsquo;t roll a Critical Failure, sorcerers may spend Power Points after rolling Spellcasting to add +1 per Power Point spent to the total.</li>\n<li>They can raise the total as much as they care to do so, perhaps turning failure into success or a raise or increasing the odds of winning an opposed roll.</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xhmLhEmiq5fK7Nak"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rqglz4nku8c"}}}
