{"_id":"eilPsXQmLERv8psJ","name":"Favored Power","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The caster has dedicated her time to mastering a particular spell, miracle, or<br />weird science device.</p>\n<p><br />Choose one of your character&rsquo;s powers. She may ignore up to two points of any<br />penalties (Multi-Action, Wounds, Fatigue, etc.) when activating that power.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.V4YHCXnNYEHC1SHS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y0bdbtf8jfd"}}}
{"_id":"f1bF2VDLavV5cj5d","name":"Trapsmith","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Many treasure hunters seek the aid of experts trapsmiths for their ability to<br />bypass dangerous booby traps. This character gets a free reroll on Repair,<br />Notice, and Thievery rolls involving traps.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Repair d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.12WR9ZUnst0L82db"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3wjknv5js85"}}}
{"_id":"iho8IARvwX7a92wG","name":"Great Power","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The sorcerer may spend a Benny to cast any single power of up to 20 Power Points at a &ndash;2 penalty to his Spellcasting roll. Leftover points are not saved. If the power fails, the sorcerer permanently loses a die type in any one attribute of his choice.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Sorcerer)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33qDMaieXxe6swpq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rqglz4nku8c"}}}
{"_id":"k55zDQ4mN2vUHdBz","name":"Great Mount","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Anyone can ride a horse, but only the greatest champions can take to the air on<br />the back of a pegasus or tame a wild griffin.</p>\n<p>This Edge grants the hero a special and powerful mount. It might be a reward for<br />some service or from his deity, he might find and wrestle into submission, or he<br />might save it from some dire fate. The Game Master should take wide liberty<br />with how the beast is encountered and tamed, perhaps even gaming it out or using<br />a Quick Encounter, but at some point of course the hero should win out and gain<br />the Edge.</p>\n<p><br />The creature is a Wild Card and its Smarts are a die type higher than others of its kind.<br />It understands simple commands and is absolutely loyal unto death. The rider and<br />mount can&rsquo;t spend Bennies for each other unless they have the Beast Bond Edge<br />(Common Bond doesn&rsquo;t count).</p>\n<p>The type of mount is up to the player and approved the Game Master. It has a<br />maximum Size of 4 (Large), and could be anything from a war horse to a pegasus to<br />a grizzly or even a great white shark (in a water-based campaign).</p>\n<p>Great Mounts don&rsquo;t advance, but instead gain one of the advantages below when its<br />master hits Legendary Rank, and every four Advances thereafter.<br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Increase one of the creature&rsquo;s Traits one die type. This may only be taken once<br />per Trait.</li>\n<li>The creature gains an Edge that makes sense for its species (GM&rsquo;s call). It must<br />meet the Requirements as usual.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Death: If the creature ever perishes, the character gains a new one, along with<br />an appropriate number of Advances. As before, this should require a quest of some<br />sort that explains how such a unique creature bonded with the hero.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Riding d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.c2e0dHRQaa28klYd"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tmcm0wr4j6l"}}}
{"_id":"kIQEcbeMnDqJpiw2","name":"Elemental Master","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Elementalists must choose an elemental origin when they become mages: earth, fire, water, or air. This Edge grants them domain over another elemental force. They may change the Trappings of their powers between the elements they&rsquo;ve mastered at will.</p>\n<p>Elemental Master may be taken multiple times to gain all four elements (or more if such exist in the Game Master&rsquo;s world).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Elementalist)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EM97gGK7t8rQyT24"},"cf":{"id":"temp_fth8tduj86b"}}}
{"_id":"kSTgHmZ3q8MePrgQ","name":"Explorer","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The world is vast, and this wanderer is called to discover its uncharted reaches.<br />When using the Travel rules (see Savage Worlds), the Explorer may make a Survival<br />roll to draw an additional card from the Action Deck (or two additional cards with<br />a raise) and choose which to use.</p>\n<p><br />In addition, the Explorer and his party reduces Travel Times by 10 percent.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hTVB4vhRyiVHWA6m"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3wjknv5js85"}}}
{"_id":"kfuDxJzZBUn1xYjL","name":"Destory Undead","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The undead are abominations to good clerics. The dead have passed on to their just rewards and should not return to the land of the living. It is little wonder then that these holy men and women are so often called to stand against the raging hordes of the undead.</p>\n<p>Evil clerics can also destroy those undead creatures that stand in their path. Perhaps it is their affinity with unnatural things, or perhaps their deity simply grants the power to clear their servants&rsquo; path to greater mayhem.</p>\n<p>As a limited action, the champion spends one Power Point to channel positive energy in a Large Blast Template centered on herself. Every undead creature within the template automatically takes 2d6 damage (or 3d6 damage for two Power Points).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Cleric), an alignment toward good"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DFE1BWSL2Q0Ifcgt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vrmmp54bah"}}}
{"_id":"lgdVQNwQ9t9koI4x","name":"Knight","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Knights are chivalric heroes dedicated to a particular cause. They swear holy oaths<br />to their patron, god, or order and must answer the call when summoned&mdash;even if<br />it means certain death.</p>\n<p>Knights are gifted with a light warhorse, lance, chain mail armor, and a medium<br />shield emblazoned with the symbol of their patron.</p>\n<p>They add +1 to Persuasion rolls when interacting with those who respect their<br />order.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+, Riding d8+, Vow (Major—a particular order, religion, or cause)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BAD5JaOAr7vfkLwD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3wjknv5js85"}}}
{"_id":"mZXUXhbyhAfbjoFt","name":"Arcane Background (Tinkerer)","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Inventors in fantasy settings rarely go on adventures. Most are firmly ensconced in their laboratories, surrounded by eclectic machines, spinning orreries, and long tables covered in bubbling concoctions.</p>\n<p>Some eventually leave their confines to explore the wider world, however, carrying portable inventions with them to protect themselves from the people and things who would do them harm.</p>\n<p>Tinkerers are highly specialized versions of the Weird Science Arcane Background who rely entirely on mechanical devices.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ARCANE SKILL: Repair (Smarts)</li>\n<li>STARTING POWERS: Any two from the list below.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>POWER POINTS: 15</li>\n<li>AVAILABLE POWERS: Blind, bolt, blast, burst, confusion, damage field, darksight, detect arcana, entangle, environmental protection, farsight, fly, light/darkness, lock/unlock, slumber, stun, wall walker.</li>\n<li>WEIRD SCIENCE: Summoners may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Weird Science).</li>\n<li>CRITICAL FAILURE: A tinkerer who rolls a Critical Failure when activating a device doesn&rsquo;t take Fatigue, but can&rsquo;t use that power again until the device is repaired (an hour&rsquo;s work and a successful Repair roll).</li>\n<li>POWERS ARE DEVICES: A tinkerer&rsquo;s powers are expressed entirely through devices, such as foldable wings for the fly power, goggles for darksight or farsight, or a&nbsp; flintlock pistol for bolt. Tinkerers can give their devices to others, allowing them to &ldquo;cast&rdquo; them using the tinkerer&rsquo;s Repair skill as their own (the ally gets a Wild Die only if they&rsquo;re also a Wild Card). This uses the tinkerer&rsquo;s Power Points as usual, and treats the ally as the caster for purposes of Range and the like. Allies may not use Power Modifiers when using the inventor&rsquo;s devices as they don&rsquo;t know how to properly &ldquo;tinker&rdquo; with them.</li>\n<li> LOST DEVICES: If an enemy takes away a tinkerer&rsquo;s device, any powers associated with it can&rsquo;t be used until it&rsquo;s recovered or remade (d6 hours x the power&rsquo;s Rank).</li>\n<li> TOOLS: Tinkerer&rsquo;s can&rsquo;t use Power Modifiers without their tool kit&mdash;a satchel, belt, or bag of spanners, screwdrivers, hammers, and other tools they use to tweak their inventions. </li>\n<li>JINX: A tinkerer can make a Repair roll on any mechanical device he can touch. If successful, the machine suffers a malfunction and stops working until it&rsquo;s fixed (a Repair roll as an action, at &ndash;2 if the tinkerer got a raise).</li>\n</ul>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smart d6+, Repair d4+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rRcJnjZI9K2RIL2L"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2doysmr4wk7"}}}
