{"_id":"ndUdaIKByzocpjyC","name":"Familiar","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>&ldquo;Familiars&rdquo; are small creatures (Size &minus;2 or &minus;3) that serve as a mage&rsquo;s loyal pet and<br />magical companion.</p>\n<p><br />Familiars are loyal to their masters but aren&rsquo;t slaves. They are very smart versions<br />of their species and can occasionally be distracted by their own inherent instincts.<br />For example, a cat might interrupt its task to chase a mouse or take a brief nap, and<br />a dog will almost certainly bark when a stranger approaches.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A familiar is a Wild Card with respect to Wounds and rolling a Wild Die with its<br />Trait rolls. It doesn&rsquo;t get Bennies, but the mage can spend his own on its behalf.<br />The familiar can understand its master&rsquo;s speech and vice-versa (others hear only the<br />creature&rsquo;s natural sounds), though concepts are limited to what a member of its species<br />might understand.</p>\n<p><br />The familiar has 5 Power Points of its own. It cannot cast spells, but the mage can draw<br />on them as if they were his own. They recharge separately and at the same rate as<br />the mage&rsquo;s.</p>\n<p>The bond between the familiar and the mage makes it immune to the beast friend<br />power cast by others. Familiars don&rsquo;t advance, but instead gain<br />one of the advantages below for each of its master&rsquo;s Ranks (including Novice) and for<br />every fourth advance the hero gains past Legendary.</p>\n<p><br />SECOND SIGHT: The owner may use the familiar&rsquo;s senses as if they were<br />her own, with a maximum range of 10 miles. She is Distracted and Vulnerable<br />while doing so.</p>\n<p><br />TRAINING: The mage can increase one of the familiar&rsquo;s Traits one die type (no<br />more than once per Trait).</p>\n<p><br />ENHANCEMENT: The familiar gains an Edge. It must make sense for the familiar&rsquo;s species (GM&rsquo;s call) and meet the Requirements as usual.</p>\n<p><br />If a familiar dies, the hero is automatically Stunned (no matter how far away she is). She<br />can summon another after 10 days and can change the type if she chooses.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Diabolist, Druid, Elementalist, Necromancer, Shaman, Sorcerer, Warlock/Witch, Wizard)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OmDX9ADo4D1RnDoT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y0bdbtf8jfd"}}}
