{"_id":"ovJVCiyg402NLD7r","name":"Really Dirty Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Your character is extremely skilled in tactical deceit. Should he get a raise on<br />a Test, he gains The Drop against that opponent until the foe is no longer<br />Shaken.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dirty Fighter"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O0AF7bsNF0c8Da7b"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
{"_id":"qHR2sFP5pJHN4VqJ","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Sneaky types with this Edge add an additional d6 to their damage when they<br />have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} on their victim, or the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. This applies to Athletics (throwing), Fighting, or Shooting attacks.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Stealth d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jm5AqtA4ajKUNTko"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9hfm5sf8y2i"}}}
{"_id":"qJj1a0sciYAoYwfs","name":"Shield Wall","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Trained soldiers can stand against overwhelming odds and furious hordes<br />with discipline, training, and a sturdy shield.</p>\n<p><br />Characters with the Shield Wall Edge (and at least a medium shield) add +1 to their Parry if they are adjacent to one ally who also has the Shield Wall Edge, and +2 if they<br />have two adjacent allies with that Edge (the maximum bonus).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Formation Fighter, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BvaUE4RE5L70Ul9A"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9hfm5sf8y2i"}}}
{"_id":"qNyx6qNzv3vGVUdv","name":"True Form","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>While shape changed, the druid can speak and cast powers at a &ndash;2 penalty even if in a form that usually wouldn&rsquo;t allow it.</p>\n<p>Some druids essentially &ldquo;live&rdquo; in their animal form, maintaining their bestial shape for days on end. Doing so gradually erodes the druid&rsquo;s humanity. For every day the druid spends more than half her time in animal form, she must make a Spirit roll. Failure reduces her Spirit a die type until she remains in human form for an entire week. If her Spirit is reduced below d4 in this manner, the druid becomes that creature forever.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Druid)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oHsEjww9nkWcq5jC"},"cf":{"id":"temp_xkxhv65se9e"}}}
{"_id":"qXXh8ZA0ahBOzy2s","name":"Undead Familiar","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The necromancer gains an undead animal companion that serves as his familiar. This works exactly as the Familiar Edge (page 36 of the Fantasy Companion) except the creature gains the Undead ability:</p>\n<p>Undead: +2 Toughness;</p>\n<p>+2 to recover from being Shaken;</p>\n<p>no additional damage from Called Shots;</p>\n<p>ignores 1 point of Wound penalties;</p>\n<p>doesn&rsquo;t breathe; immune to disease and poison.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Necromancer)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.A1xB2iEFR6V443Lt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_f045umf8w76"}}}
{"_id":"qyBhtXwHq3YDW42d","name":"Deceptive","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Lies, deception, and misdirection are a stock-in-trade for this rogue. When making a Test based on Smarts, Spirit, or linked skills, he can choose whether the target resists with Smarts or Spirit.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JvsF99UXYeNWe5Fu"},"cf":{"id":"temp_x9fec717bog"}}}
{"_id":"qyMQ3y92NMPX7b0O","name":"Chosen","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Prophecies tell of a being destined for greatness. One who will, with the help<br />of her boon companions, do great things. When the Chosen spends Conviction, it<br />lasts until the end of the encounter without having to maintain it with Bennies!</p>\n<p><br />Of course such a boon comes at a great cost. The Chosen has the Enemy (Major)<br />Hindrance&mdash;there&rsquo;s always some powerful being opposed to her quest! Worse, she has<br />a mark of some sort that can&rsquo;t be removed no matter how much she tries. It might be<br />a tattoo, birthmark, sixth finger, catlike pupils, or some other visible cosmetic<br />oddity, but those who know what to look for can find it. And by whatever narrative<br />means necessary, the mark shows through occasionally, regardless how hard she<br />attempts to cover it with clothing, wraps, or even illusions. This means the hero&rsquo;s foe<br />and his minions are always on her trail.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SttsOzv95lFHM36J"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zum629z8a7t"}}}
{"_id":"rxxdXmOLuhSfkZx5","name":"Master Chemist","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Alchemists craft permanent potions like any other (see Crafting on page 153 of the Fantasy Companion). Some are particularly adept at it, however, and can create potent potables while traveling using alternate ingredients.</p>\n<p>Master Alchemist allows the scientist to create potions at half the usual cost and as if she had access to Simple Workshop as long as she has her alchemist&rsquo;s bag or makeshift supplies the GM feels contain necessary ingredients or reasonable facsimiles.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Alchemist), Alchemy d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.F5xaWw5OOVbQ0jgM"},"cf":{"id":"temp_rtqi0xm40m"}}}
