{"_id":"wbhDHxdCopr7jmMR","name":"Endurance","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Fighters, barbarians, gladiators and the like learn to endure violent lives filled<br />with merciless brutality. A character with this Edge has learned to survive under the<br />most relentless conditions. She gets a free reroll on Soak rolls.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TaxM3yyxHO6hHX89"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
{"_id":"whDcNTAT831G4dGd","name":"Favored Terrain","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Rangers, druids, and those who spend great amounts of time in the wilderness<br />know how to use it to their advantage.<br /><br />Choose a terrain type (Arctic, Aquatic, Desert, Forest, Hill/Mountain, Jungle,<br />Plains, Swamp, Urban, or Underground). The character draws an additional Action<br />Card for initiative when in his Favored Terrain. He may then choose from all<br />possible Action Cards as usual.</p>\n<p>Favored Terrain may be taken multiple<br />times, adding a new Favored Terrain each<br />time.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Survival d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PEj147JnFVLP7C7f"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zum629z8a7t"}}}
{"_id":"wqB8TzdaZ3sw8ZbM","name":"Great Summoning","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The mage can conjure beasts most others can&rsquo;t, including a barghest for 5 points, a mammoth for 7 points, a frost mammoth for 8 points, a tyrannosaurus rex for 8 points, or a drake for 9 points.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Arcane Background (Summoner), summon animal, summon monster"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kySAjWHwEKM9s81m"},"cf":{"id":"temp_txmjdapapja"}}}
{"_id":"wqzXAzGmy3DqdZ2J","name":"Heirloom","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Occasionally, powerful magic items wind up in the hands of relatively novice<br />adventures. This Edge grants your hero one magic item (or a themed set, GM&rsquo;s call)<br />chosen from those listed in Chapter Five with a total value of $10,000 each time this<br />Edge is taken.</p>\n<p><br />This is a one-time only benefit&mdash;if the item is destroyed or is a consumable (like<br />a potion), it isn&rsquo;t replenished. If it&rsquo;s lost, it must be recovered through adventure!</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JxyXSTxRfona0OOq"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zum629z8a7t"}}}
{"_id":"wy3JBAJasnr6nx6E","name":"Legendary Mount","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Nothing speaks of a character&rsquo;s power and renown like riding a great and terrible dragon, war mammoth, or rampaging dinosaur into battle!</p>\n<p>The hero has befriended and can ride such a beast&mdash;most any non-unique creature in the bestiary with the Game Master&rsquo;s permission. The mount is Loyal to its master but strong-willed and has the Resilient Monstrous Ability.</p>\n<p>Death: If the mount perishes, another takes its place eventually, perhaps after a long narrative trek or several encounters that describe how the beast and rider form their bond.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Riding d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.O6KplTyTF2Wwt4wU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ult6pu9nb1"}}}
{"_id":"xiw3waGRS2ZnRNH1","name":"Scout","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Scouts are masters of navigating the mystic lands of their fantastic worlds. When the<br />Game Master draws a face card while the party is traveling (see the Encounter rules<br />under Travel in Savage Worlds) the Scout may make a Notice roll at &minus;2 to detect the<br />hazard, creature, or event first.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Scouts are always considered alert for Notice rolls versus Stealth, ignore up to<br />2 points of penalties on Survival rolls to track, and on a raise gain more specific<br />information about what they&rsquo;re following. They also add +2 to Common Knowledge<br />rolls to recall information about towns, outposts, landmarks, or lairs along a<br />particular route they may have traveled before (player and GM&rsquo;s call).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Woodsman"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XejpnR3m2qkW2xuU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9lrkhtldl9e"}}}
{"_id":"xrGBopLGNHg6Fcrj","name":"Sunder","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Those who spend their lives working with stone and other natural materials not only<br />know how to craft tools with them&mdash;they also know how to break them.</p>\n<p><br />When striking to break an object, the sunderer adds +d6 to his damage total.<br />Damage dice may still not Ace, however (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Breaking Things} in Savage Worlds).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qRQvsz55vjhxa5QB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9hfm5sf8y2i"}}}
{"_id":"ySeRcZH1LGthQaRY","name":"Dirge","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This baleful performance builds dread among the bard&rsquo;s foes. At the bard&rsquo;s discretion, any enemy within 10&rdquo; (20 yards) and line of sight who spends a Benny to Soak or reroll a Trait or damage roll subtracts 2 from the total.</p>\n<p>The bard must be able to speak, sing, or play her instrument to use this ability.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Arcane Background (Bard)"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zTuxScgNkZ0LBTif"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2jnavlrmj8e"}}}
{"_id":"zJYlzo9Dewl4E0lm","name":"Epic Mastery","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The spellcaster is so well-versed in her arcane or divine craft that she has learned<br />new ways to manipulate her powers. She gains access to the Epic Power Modifiers<br />for all her Powers.</p>\n<p><br />Epic Mastery applies to all a character&rsquo;s Arcane Backgrounds if she has more than<br />one, though she must meet the arcane skill requirement for each before she can<br />use Epic Modifiers with that background&rsquo;s powers.</p>\n<p><br />See Chapter Four in the Fantasy Companion for a complete list of Epic Power modifiers.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d6+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6ACB98R2933lbOYt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_y0bdbtf8jfd"}}}
{"_id":"zRp8uJSaWH1vCxTG","name":"Close Fighting","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up<br />close and personal.</p>\n<p><br />Close fighters move inside most weapons&rsquo; reach, adding a bonus to their Parry equal<br />to an enemy weapon&rsquo;s Reach. No bonus is granted if the foe is unarmed or using a<br />knife or other small weapon.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Zc9jPcQiS5H2aa6O"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9hfm5sf8y2i"}}}
{"_id":"zTHcdtF040hGNYDd","name":"Triple Shot","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The archer may increase the Rate of Fire to 3 by firing three<br />projectiles at once. This is a limited action with the same limit as Double Shot.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Double Shot, Shooting d10+"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VNGRwz21B7wR6fFt"},"cf":{"id":"temp_xffypo4gk8"}}}
{"_id":"zXc4PZKrKaD0dBFQ","name":"Opportunistic","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Opportunity is what one makes of it. When a character with this Edge is dealt a Joker,<br />he adds +4 to his Trait and damage rolls instead of +2.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.90gHTP3upTCFKTAD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9zgghs3jjem"}}}
{"_id":"zc7RB18jU2NrAARo","name":"Dirty Fighter","type":"edge","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Those with this Edge will do anything to win a fight. The dastardly cur is particularly<br />good at tricks. He adds +2 to rolls when performing a Test with the Fighting skill.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"favorite":false,"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"0llfus6nG1V829T5":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Pi8jK4llCwgh1KHi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_q3rzfx4a0po"}}}
